1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:00:56,661 --> 00:00:58,121
Please let me say goodbye

4
00:00:59,914 --> 00:01:02,041
to Tae-seo in person before I go.

5
00:01:06,629 --> 00:01:09,132
I know you guys don't come out
when it gets cold.

6
00:01:10,717 --> 00:01:11,551
But still…

7
00:01:13,803 --> 00:01:14,971
Mo Eun-a.

8
00:01:28,902 --> 00:01:35,533
STILL SHINING

9
00:01:40,955 --> 00:01:44,459
All the places in this town look the same
no matter how far you go.

10
00:01:45,668 --> 00:01:47,337
Are we even getting close?

11
00:01:54,969 --> 00:01:56,846
The fireflies…

12
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:00,141
I know they don't come out
when it's cold, but…

13
00:02:00,225 --> 00:02:01,184
What are you…

14
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:05,438
doing here?

15
00:02:14,155 --> 00:02:15,156
Hey, isn't that Tae-seo?

16
00:02:16,074 --> 00:02:16,908
Tae-seo!

17
00:02:21,829 --> 00:02:23,122
Im A-sol, get out.

18
00:02:24,874 --> 00:02:26,501
Tae-seo, you drive instead!

19
00:02:26,584 --> 00:02:28,670
You know where the restaurant is!

20
00:02:28,753 --> 00:02:30,213
The road here is really confusing!

21
00:02:30,296 --> 00:02:31,339
I'm tired!

22
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:35,593
I drove all the way here!

23
00:02:35,677 --> 00:02:37,512
I'm so tired!

24
00:02:40,723 --> 00:02:42,392
Who is he talking with?

25
00:02:46,896 --> 00:02:48,481
I'm cold!

26
00:02:49,565 --> 00:02:50,525
Come on.

27
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:53,736
Gosh.

28
00:03:02,203 --> 00:03:03,830
He hasn't changed one bit.

29
00:03:04,414 --> 00:03:06,124
I used to take really good care of him.

30
00:03:06,207 --> 00:03:07,625
People thought he was my brother.

31
00:03:07,709 --> 00:03:09,794
He looks more like me, not Tae-seo.

32
00:03:09,877 --> 00:03:13,089
What are you talking about?
He's clearly a cuter version of Tae-seo.

33
00:03:13,172 --> 00:03:14,799
I get that a lot.

34
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:16,843
We just have different vibes.

35
00:03:16,926 --> 00:03:18,386
A-sol, let me pour you a glass.

36
00:03:18,469 --> 00:03:20,805
Thank you for inviting us.

37
00:03:20,888 --> 00:03:22,724
-It looks delicious.
-Right?

38
00:03:22,807 --> 00:03:26,602
They have the best seafood ramyeon
and aged kimchi here.

39
00:03:26,686 --> 00:03:28,938
They only bring out
the aged kimchi for me.

40
00:03:30,982 --> 00:03:33,026
Tae-seo left Seoul right away
for your sake.

41
00:03:33,109 --> 00:03:34,777
He didn't hesitate at all.

42
00:03:34,861 --> 00:03:36,320
Now that I'm here, I can see why.

43
00:03:36,404 --> 00:03:38,448
When he was in Seoul,
he always looked so worn out.

44
00:03:38,531 --> 00:03:40,408
But here, the ocean's right there,

45
00:03:40,491 --> 00:03:42,118
the sky's clear, and the air's fresh.

46
00:03:43,411 --> 00:03:45,371
Man, it's nice here.

47
00:03:46,414 --> 00:03:48,207
Wait, so that's what you meant.

48
00:03:48,291 --> 00:03:50,752
"My dad looks at the sky at work,

49
00:03:50,835 --> 00:03:52,795
and my mom looks
at the sky and ocean at work."

50
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:55,173
He said it was
the best job in the universe.

51
00:03:56,090 --> 00:03:58,134
That's what Mom used to say.

52
00:03:58,217 --> 00:03:59,552
You still remember it, Tae-seo?

53
00:03:59,635 --> 00:04:01,721
Of course, he does.

54
00:04:01,804 --> 00:04:04,390
Man, you were on crutches
the last time I saw you.

55
00:04:04,474 --> 00:04:05,933
You walk so well now. I'm proud.

56
00:04:06,017 --> 00:04:08,770
Come on. That's ancient history.

57
00:04:09,562 --> 00:04:12,398
-Is your dad doing well?
-More than well.

58
00:04:12,482 --> 00:04:14,233
Hey, come on.

59
00:04:14,317 --> 00:04:16,235
You need to drive us back to Seoul.

60
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,820
I need to visit the hospital.

61
00:04:17,904 --> 00:04:18,905
Tae-seo.

62
00:04:19,655 --> 00:04:20,490
Just go.

63
00:04:21,157 --> 00:04:24,285
Your guests came all the way here.
You should take them back to Seoul.

64
00:04:24,369 --> 00:04:26,746
Even Hyeong-seok's here,
and he never comes.

65
00:04:26,829 --> 00:04:28,873
You're making it awkward for him to drink.

66
00:04:28,956 --> 00:04:30,750
Did you miss me that much,
my little brother?

67
00:04:31,334 --> 00:04:32,543
Have a drink.

68
00:04:32,627 --> 00:04:34,670
You can even drink now.
You're all grown up.

69
00:04:34,754 --> 00:04:35,588
Oh, come on.

70
00:04:42,261 --> 00:04:44,806
The lights on the bicycle were broken.

71
00:04:46,432 --> 00:04:48,726
The girl on the bicycle earlier
was your ex, right?

72
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,650
So she lives in Gangneung.

73
00:04:56,734 --> 00:04:57,568
She doesn't.

74
00:05:00,113 --> 00:05:01,406
Then, where does she live?

75
00:05:02,448 --> 00:05:03,616
I don't know.

76
00:05:05,201 --> 00:05:06,411
Why did she come here?

77
00:05:08,329 --> 00:05:10,039
I don't know.

78
00:05:10,123 --> 00:05:11,749
So you didn't get to talk to her.

79
00:05:13,126 --> 00:05:15,837
You must be frustrated and curious.

80
00:05:41,445 --> 00:05:43,990
MO EUN-A

81
00:05:44,574 --> 00:05:46,367
MO EUN-A

82
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:50,872
Why were you in Yeonwoo…

83
00:06:33,497 --> 00:06:35,249
Tae-seo's here.

84
00:06:37,210 --> 00:06:38,502
Yes, I'm here.

85
00:06:40,463 --> 00:06:42,757
You must be having such a hard time.

86
00:06:43,841 --> 00:06:47,845
Get plenty of rest
while you're on leave from the military.

87
00:06:52,558 --> 00:06:53,392
What's this?

88
00:06:54,435 --> 00:06:56,020
At least tell me if you're coming.

89
00:06:56,103 --> 00:06:58,231
I didn't even eat before I came here.

90
00:06:58,314 --> 00:07:00,316
Did you get to talk with Grandma?

91
00:07:01,567 --> 00:07:03,486
She talked about
when I was in the military.

92
00:07:03,569 --> 00:07:05,613
She'd always talk about
my middle school days.

93
00:07:05,696 --> 00:07:06,989
Time must've passed for her.

94
00:07:10,785 --> 00:07:13,162
Have you seen Eun-a
from the house at the end?

95
00:07:13,955 --> 00:07:15,373
Why suddenly mention that name?

96
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:18,042
I thought I saw her.

97
00:07:20,419 --> 00:07:21,712
I don't want you being pathetic.

98
00:07:23,714 --> 00:07:26,926
Just live an ordinary life.
Get married and have kids.

99
00:07:27,009 --> 00:07:28,219
Come visit from time to time.

100
00:07:28,302 --> 00:07:29,512
Is that too much to ask?

101
00:07:29,595 --> 00:07:30,846
I'm going to live alone,

102
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:34,183
and then send our grandparents off
to be with Mom and Dad.

103
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:35,268
I'll do all of that.

104
00:07:35,351 --> 00:07:37,144
Did you see her or not?

105
00:07:37,228 --> 00:07:38,646
You didn't even answer me.

106
00:07:39,689 --> 00:07:41,023
I'm off.

107
00:08:05,423 --> 00:08:06,549
Hold on, please.

108
00:08:19,687 --> 00:08:22,898
Eun-a should be here by now,
but she's late.

109
00:08:22,982 --> 00:08:25,443
She went out with that old, beat-up bike.

110
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:28,154
You need to hurry and find her.

111
00:08:30,072 --> 00:08:31,824
Right.

112
00:11:16,614 --> 00:11:17,865
What are you doing here?

113
00:11:17,948 --> 00:11:20,618
I came to take a quick look
around our school.

114
00:11:21,452 --> 00:11:22,786
I had no idea it had closed down.

115
00:11:23,454 --> 00:11:24,580
Not that.

116
00:11:24,663 --> 00:11:27,082
Why here? In Yeonwoo.

117
00:11:29,752 --> 00:11:31,170
Are you staying here for good?

118
00:11:32,338 --> 00:11:33,589
No, just for a bit.

119
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,885
I'm going to stay with Park So-hyeon.

120
00:11:40,429 --> 00:11:41,764
This is great.

121
00:11:41,847 --> 00:11:44,433
Even though I was worried
about running into you here,

122
00:11:44,517 --> 00:11:48,521
I still wanted to tell you
that I was leaving to live with So-hyeon.

123
00:11:50,397 --> 00:11:51,732
I wanted to say a quick goodbye

124
00:11:52,858 --> 00:11:54,652
and tell you in person too.

125
00:11:56,529 --> 00:11:57,613
And now, I got to do that.

126
00:11:59,532 --> 00:12:01,492
My bicycle lights are broken.

127
00:12:01,575 --> 00:12:03,911
You can follow me from behind then.

128
00:12:04,995 --> 00:12:06,539
This is great.

129
00:12:06,622 --> 00:12:09,041
I was worried
I'd have to push my bicycle back.

130
00:12:09,124 --> 00:12:11,794
Remember the fork in the road
where we always used to split up?

131
00:12:12,461 --> 00:12:14,004
Let's say goodbye there.

132
00:12:14,713 --> 00:12:16,757
I really wanted to do this with you.

133
00:12:18,259 --> 00:12:19,093
This is great.

134
00:12:21,679 --> 00:12:22,763
When are you leaving?

135
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:25,140
Soon.

136
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:27,935
Since we've met,

137
00:12:29,311 --> 00:12:30,396
let's say goodbye.

138
00:12:31,564 --> 00:12:33,607
I really wanted to do that with you.

139
00:12:35,568 --> 00:12:36,944
Bye, then.

140
00:12:39,822 --> 00:12:40,990
I'm off.

141
00:15:14,935 --> 00:15:15,936
It's me.

142
00:15:19,189 --> 00:15:20,357
I know.

143
00:15:23,235 --> 00:15:24,778
Nothing happened, right?

144
00:15:26,447 --> 00:15:27,823
I…

145
00:15:27,906 --> 00:15:31,535
I left you alone
with that colleague of yours.

146
00:15:33,579 --> 00:15:35,914
It didn't cause trouble for you, right?

147
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,251
Why…

148
00:15:40,419 --> 00:15:42,212
Why are you worried about me?

149
00:15:44,465 --> 00:15:45,924
There's no need.

150
00:15:48,552 --> 00:15:50,220
You had absolutely

151
00:15:52,222 --> 00:15:53,807
nothing to worry about.

152
00:15:57,227 --> 00:15:58,604
There was no need…

153
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:01,899
I guess so.

154
00:16:01,982 --> 00:16:05,110
I can still picture that field
in my mind clearly,

155
00:16:06,361 --> 00:16:08,530
so I wondered
if you'd finished things properly.

156
00:16:10,741 --> 00:16:13,911
I wondered if leaving a place
you had poured your heart and soul into

157
00:16:15,037 --> 00:16:16,580
wasn't too hard on you.

158
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:21,293
I wondered why you were
always forced to leave

159
00:16:22,836 --> 00:16:25,089
when you never wanted to.

160
00:16:27,758 --> 00:16:28,842
There was no need,

161
00:16:32,596 --> 00:16:35,224
but I kept wondering.

162
00:16:41,814 --> 00:16:43,649
Why is Park So-hyeon your mom?

163
00:16:43,732 --> 00:16:45,442
Actually,

164
00:16:45,526 --> 00:16:48,695
it's more that her mom is my grandmother.

165
00:16:50,322 --> 00:16:51,323
She's a good person.

166
00:16:52,032 --> 00:16:55,869
You didn't make a bad decision
because you felt trapped, right?

167
00:16:56,662 --> 00:16:59,790
-When you feel trapped--
-No, Tae-seo.

168
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:04,586
I went to Tongyeong.

169
00:17:05,337 --> 00:17:07,381
Your guesthouse was closed,

170
00:17:08,048 --> 00:17:10,008
and I was told you had gone to your mom's.

171
00:17:11,009 --> 00:17:13,846
I thought it was the mom
who lives far away

172
00:17:14,805 --> 00:17:16,515
and likes noodles.

173
00:17:17,891 --> 00:17:19,393
We missed each other.

174
00:17:21,019 --> 00:17:22,771
We're really good at that.

175
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,402
OLD HOUSE IM A-SOL

176
00:17:39,121 --> 00:17:40,164
I should hang up.

177
00:17:40,247 --> 00:17:41,582
Granny's going to wake up.

178
00:17:41,665 --> 00:17:43,041
Bye.

179
00:17:45,335 --> 00:17:46,170
Eun…

180
00:17:56,763 --> 00:18:00,726
Including meetings and a year-end party,
I had three events to attend.

181
00:18:00,809 --> 00:18:02,603
The venue was around here,

182
00:18:02,686 --> 00:18:04,271
so I just stopped by.

183
00:18:07,232 --> 00:18:08,442
Were you drinking?

184
00:18:09,443 --> 00:18:11,111
Yeah, just a little.

185
00:18:12,571 --> 00:18:13,405
Sorry.

186
00:18:14,865 --> 00:18:16,408
No need to apologize for drinking.

187
00:18:19,578 --> 00:18:20,621
Should I go?

188
00:18:21,205 --> 00:18:22,539
If you're tired, I'll go.

189
00:18:25,834 --> 00:18:27,794
Let's go out for a drink.

190
00:18:27,878 --> 00:18:29,213
I need to talk to you.

191
00:18:32,257 --> 00:18:34,718
I wanted to finish what we were watching.

192
00:18:36,011 --> 00:18:36,970
Sure.

193
00:18:41,099 --> 00:18:43,018
I saw a bungeoppang place on the way here.

194
00:18:43,101 --> 00:18:44,603
But there was nowhere to park.

195
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,396
I'll go buy you some.

196
00:18:50,108 --> 00:18:50,943
You can sit.

197
00:18:51,026 --> 00:18:51,860
Okay.

198
00:19:27,229 --> 00:19:28,063
This is nice.

199
00:19:31,525 --> 00:19:35,821
It's nice to relax together like this
after a crazy day at work.

200
00:19:43,370 --> 00:19:44,830
Just one sip.

201
00:19:44,913 --> 00:19:46,373
I can leave my car here.

202
00:19:55,549 --> 00:19:56,383
Focus.

203
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:13,442
HAE-JIN

204
00:20:14,443 --> 00:20:17,863
Hi, Eun-a.
Sorry for calling you at this hour.

205
00:20:17,946 --> 00:20:18,905
It's kind of urgent.

206
00:20:18,989 --> 00:20:21,074
Could you cover for me
for just three hours tomorrow?

207
00:20:21,658 --> 00:20:24,703
You just need to check in
one guest at 3:00 p.m.

208
00:20:50,062 --> 00:20:51,897
Gosh, sorry about the wait.

209
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,732
There was just so much traffic today.

210
00:20:53,815 --> 00:20:56,485
Look at you dressed all properly
for just a few hours of work.

211
00:20:56,568 --> 00:20:58,236
You're such a professional.

212
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,821
What do you want to eat?

213
00:20:59,905 --> 00:21:01,365
It's my treat, so let's go.

214
00:21:01,448 --> 00:21:03,325
I've got a bus to catch.

215
00:21:03,408 --> 00:21:05,243
Did you really just come to help me out?

216
00:21:05,994 --> 00:21:07,621
I'm touched.

217
00:21:08,663 --> 00:21:10,499
You sure you're not here to see someone?

218
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:15,128
There is someone, right?

219
00:21:15,879 --> 00:21:18,215
I knew it.
If you came to see them, you should.

220
00:21:24,429 --> 00:21:25,555
I did.

221
00:21:27,557 --> 00:21:29,684
Someone I wanted to see,
even for a moment.

222
00:21:33,522 --> 00:21:35,232
I already saw him.

223
00:21:56,753 --> 00:22:01,258
YEON NAMSAN

224
00:22:30,662 --> 00:22:31,538
So-hyeon.

225
00:22:32,831 --> 00:22:34,916
I might arrive later than planned.

226
00:22:35,542 --> 00:22:36,793
I'll get back to you.

227
00:23:51,576 --> 00:23:53,203
This is where I stop.

228
00:24:05,298 --> 00:24:08,093
Trying to make things work,

229
00:24:09,803 --> 00:24:12,055
intruding into your peaceful life,

230
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:15,517
and repeating this vicious cycle.

231
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,685
Enough.

232
00:24:27,696 --> 00:24:29,197
Are you crazy?

233
00:24:29,281 --> 00:24:32,367
Do you know how much the fees would be
if you canceled your flight now?

234
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:34,411
At the hotel you worked at ten years ago,

235
00:24:34,494 --> 00:24:36,830
your former coworker
is now the assistant manager.

236
00:24:36,913 --> 00:24:40,250
They're all waiting for you to come back,

237
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:42,002
not to mention my mom.

238
00:24:42,085 --> 00:24:44,087
Everyone's waiting for you.

239
00:24:46,798 --> 00:24:48,258
I'll go as planned.

240
00:24:49,509 --> 00:24:51,761
I'll keep my promise.

241
00:24:55,432 --> 00:24:56,683
Dad.

242
00:24:56,766 --> 00:25:00,478
When you told me to live freely,
as if I was on a journey,

243
00:25:01,354 --> 00:25:04,649
you meant that in life,
we can't stay even when we want to.

244
00:25:05,233 --> 00:25:07,360
Things seem like they'll last forever,
but they don't.

245
00:25:09,654 --> 00:25:12,240
And since life is full of such things,

246
00:25:12,324 --> 00:25:14,159
when it's time to leave,

247
00:25:14,909 --> 00:25:17,454
you meant I should just take off,
as if I was on a journey.

248
00:25:20,540 --> 00:25:24,836
Now at age 30, I finally understand this.

249
00:25:34,554 --> 00:25:37,223
MISSED CALL
EUN-A

250
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:48,777
MART

251
00:25:52,489 --> 00:25:53,323
It's cold outside.

252
00:26:00,955 --> 00:26:02,123
Give me one second.

253
00:26:42,038 --> 00:26:46,751
When my dad and I first came here,
we had just one bag with us.

254
00:26:47,502 --> 00:26:49,379
It's in the main bedroom dresser.

255
00:26:49,462 --> 00:26:51,172
It should be in the bottom drawer.

256
00:26:51,256 --> 00:26:53,466
It's a backpack that you use for hiking.

257
00:26:54,926 --> 00:26:57,303
Can you get it for me?

258
00:27:17,699 --> 00:27:19,242
Is this the one?

259
00:27:19,325 --> 00:27:20,785
Yeah, it is.

260
00:27:24,539 --> 00:27:26,291
This should be enough to take with me.

261
00:27:27,208 --> 00:27:29,961
I thought I wouldn't be able
to take anything from here.

262
00:27:30,044 --> 00:27:31,504
But I got something thanks to you.

263
00:27:34,883 --> 00:27:36,926
You've never been
in our kitchen before, right?

264
00:27:37,010 --> 00:27:38,595
This is the best part of our house.

265
00:27:38,678 --> 00:27:40,847
I'm sure you didn't call
to show me your kitchen.

266
00:27:43,683 --> 00:27:46,102
I went to Seoul
because I had something to do.

267
00:27:46,853 --> 00:27:49,147
And since it's Seoul,
Yeon Namsan was right there…

268
00:27:50,023 --> 00:27:51,649
I thought of you, so I called.

269
00:27:54,194 --> 00:27:55,862
I called without even thinking,

270
00:27:56,946 --> 00:27:58,531
but now that I see you here,

271
00:27:58,615 --> 00:28:00,200
I think I know why I did that.

272
00:28:01,743 --> 00:28:04,370
I guess I wanted to do this with you.

273
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:09,709
Let's go over there.

274
00:28:22,096 --> 00:28:23,473
This is yours.

275
00:28:35,068 --> 00:28:37,320
I finally got to offer you some tea.

276
00:28:43,284 --> 00:28:44,410
I'm…

277
00:28:46,412 --> 00:28:48,289
leaving on Friday.

278
00:28:52,460 --> 00:28:53,378
That's pretty soon.

279
00:29:04,848 --> 00:29:08,017
You were right. I felt trapped,
so Park So-hyeon became my mom.

280
00:29:10,311 --> 00:29:12,605
That's what it took for me to allow that.

281
00:29:16,901 --> 00:29:18,611
But to put it differently,

282
00:29:20,029 --> 00:29:22,115
I was able to make up my mind
thanks to you.

283
00:29:25,952 --> 00:29:29,455
I'd been thinking for a while
that maybe I should accept her as family.

284
00:29:30,081 --> 00:29:33,418
My dad at least left me Park So-hyeon
before he left.

285
00:29:34,210 --> 00:29:35,503
That's how I see it now.

286
00:29:38,172 --> 00:29:39,674
I'm saying it's not your fault.

287
00:29:40,717 --> 00:29:41,926
It's thanks to you.

288
00:29:43,303 --> 00:29:45,138
That's how I've always felt about you.

289
00:29:48,641 --> 00:29:50,268
It's all thanks to you in the end.

290
00:29:51,436 --> 00:29:54,606
But you probably feel
the exact opposite about me.

291
00:29:55,815 --> 00:29:56,858
If you go…

292
00:29:59,235 --> 00:30:00,528
will you come back?

293
00:30:00,612 --> 00:30:02,196
Right now,

294
00:30:02,780 --> 00:30:04,407
I don't plan to.

295
00:30:07,201 --> 00:30:08,661
Where will you be living?

296
00:30:08,745 --> 00:30:10,204
At Park So-hyeon's mom's place.

297
00:30:10,288 --> 00:30:12,165
The lady who'll become my grandmother.

298
00:30:12,248 --> 00:30:13,583
They don't live together.

299
00:30:13,666 --> 00:30:14,542
What about work?

300
00:30:14,626 --> 00:30:16,669
I can work right away too.

301
00:30:18,838 --> 00:30:20,632
Park So-hyeon told me

302
00:30:20,715 --> 00:30:24,218
the hotel I worked at ten years ago
is waiting for me to return,

303
00:30:25,929 --> 00:30:26,930
so I should go.

304
00:30:28,056 --> 00:30:31,392
It's kind of amazing
that they still remember me.

305
00:30:31,476 --> 00:30:32,727
I liked it there.

306
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:34,479
But…

307
00:30:35,813 --> 00:30:37,523
If I hadn't gone there…

308
00:30:42,946 --> 00:30:44,197
If I hadn't left…

309
00:30:47,867 --> 00:30:50,161
That's all I kept thinking about
for the past ten years.

310
00:30:53,998 --> 00:30:56,084
But I think I can finally go back now.

311
00:31:02,215 --> 00:31:03,716
You'll have a place to stay,

312
00:31:04,884 --> 00:31:06,386
your grandmother will be there,

313
00:31:07,220 --> 00:31:08,846
and you'll have a job.

314
00:31:17,146 --> 00:31:18,064
Why…

315
00:31:19,190 --> 00:31:20,984
did you go to Tongyeong?

316
00:31:22,819 --> 00:31:26,447
I couldn't understand
why things were like this between us.

317
00:31:29,534 --> 00:31:30,785
Everything felt wrong.

318
00:31:31,828 --> 00:31:33,663
You had every reason to do that.

319
00:31:34,872 --> 00:31:37,000
My decision when I was 20 was wrong,

320
00:31:38,418 --> 00:31:39,502
but yours was right.

321
00:31:47,427 --> 00:31:48,553
Do you realize

322
00:31:48,636 --> 00:31:50,972
we're worried about each other right now?

323
00:31:52,306 --> 00:31:53,391
Because for us,

324
00:31:54,726 --> 00:31:56,394
we can't make things hard for each other.

325
00:31:58,646 --> 00:32:00,148
No matter where we are.

326
00:32:05,778 --> 00:32:07,739
You're the only one in the world
who's like that.

327
00:32:13,953 --> 00:32:17,081
I told you I logged into your account
and listened to music twice.

328
00:32:18,374 --> 00:32:19,625
Both times happened here.

329
00:32:26,174 --> 00:32:28,009
PLAYLIST

330
00:32:28,092 --> 00:32:29,844
It was December.

331
00:32:31,512 --> 00:32:34,307
I had caught a cold after shoveling
all the snow in the village.

332
00:32:35,475 --> 00:32:37,560
I had decided on interning in Hawaii.

333
00:32:41,105 --> 00:32:44,025
And I had finally accepted
that we broke up.

334
00:32:46,903 --> 00:32:51,199
Then, when I gave up on everything
in Tongyeong and came here,

335
00:32:51,783 --> 00:32:53,284
even before leaving for Seoul…

336
00:32:55,828 --> 00:32:57,747
When I logged into your account…

337
00:33:00,958 --> 00:33:01,918
Look at me.

338
00:33:03,169 --> 00:33:06,714
…it felt like I was looking at you.

339
00:33:10,468 --> 00:33:11,803
Even when I'm far away,

340
00:33:13,012 --> 00:33:16,224
if I need to borrow your strength,
I'm logging into your account.

341
00:33:18,101 --> 00:33:19,352
You don't mind, right?

342
00:33:21,521 --> 00:33:22,480
If you go there,

343
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,483
will you smile like that?

344
00:33:30,738 --> 00:33:32,490
I don't like her.

345
00:33:34,534 --> 00:33:37,120
She's so cheerful,
completely unaware of what's ahead.

346
00:33:39,914 --> 00:33:41,249
I like her.

347
00:33:45,962 --> 00:33:47,046
Then…

348
00:33:50,508 --> 00:33:52,260
I should try to be like her.

349
00:33:54,595 --> 00:33:55,721
I'll do that.

350
00:33:59,225 --> 00:34:00,184
I should go.

351
00:35:19,555 --> 00:35:21,766
Eun-a, let's eat.

352
00:35:24,227 --> 00:35:27,230
It makes me so happy to cook for you.

353
00:35:27,939 --> 00:35:29,982
I'm done. There's a lot of things
to do around here.

354
00:35:30,816 --> 00:35:32,443
What are you going to do today?

355
00:35:33,527 --> 00:35:34,862
I'm going to drop by my house.

356
00:35:35,696 --> 00:35:37,740
I just want to clean the kitchen.

357
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:40,618
You're going to go inside?

358
00:35:42,745 --> 00:35:43,913
Just the kitchen.

359
00:35:45,873 --> 00:35:47,959
Okay, already. I'll come visit.

360
00:35:50,628 --> 00:35:52,129
-Thanks for everything.
-All the best.

361
00:35:52,922 --> 00:35:54,257
It's been a pleasure.

362
00:36:30,001 --> 00:36:32,003
I thought this would be
an invalid number by now.

363
00:36:33,087 --> 00:36:35,840
Dong-sik told me you're leaving Korea.

364
00:36:36,632 --> 00:36:37,717
I'm leaving soon.

365
00:36:38,718 --> 00:36:41,804
If you have something to say, go ahead.
I'm sure you resent me.

366
00:36:53,816 --> 00:36:55,192
I'm not really one to talk,

367
00:36:55,985 --> 00:36:57,820
but back then, I thought you'd abandoned

368
00:36:57,903 --> 00:37:00,031
the guesthouse you loved
because of that guy.

369
00:37:00,614 --> 00:37:03,284
I was so angry,
wondering what my efforts were all for.

370
00:37:04,493 --> 00:37:06,620
But once I'd calmed down…

371
00:37:08,122 --> 00:37:11,584
-Back then--
-I didn't plan to go there and meet him.

372
00:37:11,667 --> 00:37:14,086
I really did run into him
by chance in Seoul.

373
00:37:16,714 --> 00:37:19,467
And I tried my best to bring
what I'd started to a proper close.

374
00:37:21,427 --> 00:37:23,137
Not that you'd believe me.

375
00:37:24,180 --> 00:37:25,765
Is that what you wanted to say?

376
00:37:27,641 --> 00:37:29,268
To be fair, running into people happens.

377
00:37:30,061 --> 00:37:31,687
You remember the girl I went out with?

378
00:37:31,771 --> 00:37:33,356
Your roommate during your intern days.

379
00:37:34,732 --> 00:37:36,192
I remember.

380
00:37:36,275 --> 00:37:39,320
She said how you looked
in your hotel uniform

381
00:37:39,403 --> 00:37:41,155
and in regular clothes
was really different.

382
00:37:41,739 --> 00:37:44,533
She said you didn't look good
in regular clothes. It was ridiculous.

383
00:37:44,617 --> 00:37:46,285
You said the same thing back then.

384
00:37:47,119 --> 00:37:49,163
You said that excuse was ridiculous.

385
00:37:50,539 --> 00:37:53,667
I ran into someone I dated in Gangneung
all the way in Geoje Island.

386
00:37:54,585 --> 00:37:55,961
It does happen.

387
00:37:56,962 --> 00:37:58,381
In all my life,

388
00:37:58,464 --> 00:38:01,675
you were the first person
who listened to me so attentively

389
00:38:02,843 --> 00:38:05,137
and respected what I said.

390
00:38:07,348 --> 00:38:08,599
And I'm nobody special.

391
00:38:09,642 --> 00:38:11,811
You're someone I care enough
to worry about.

392
00:38:13,062 --> 00:38:15,398
I'm relieved you're going to live
with Park So-hyeon.

393
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:19,193
When I left this job,
I was wondering why I felt so empty.

394
00:38:20,486 --> 00:38:22,488
It was because
you had been there at every step.

395
00:38:23,572 --> 00:38:25,866
Without your feedback,

396
00:38:25,950 --> 00:38:28,160
I found myself without dreams or anything.

397
00:38:28,244 --> 00:38:30,162
I'd planned to just get by in life,

398
00:38:31,956 --> 00:38:34,667
but I ended up pushing myself
to keep up with you.

399
00:38:36,127 --> 00:38:37,461
For those ten years of my life…

400
00:38:39,296 --> 00:38:41,507
only you know how hard I worked.

401
00:38:43,259 --> 00:38:45,010
I'll vouch for that.

402
00:38:45,886 --> 00:38:50,391
I'll be the one to vouch
for how you gave it everything you had.

403
00:38:51,392 --> 00:38:52,560
That's enough for me.

404
00:38:56,522 --> 00:38:57,940
Take care.

405
00:39:00,276 --> 00:39:01,277
You too.

406
00:39:03,028 --> 00:39:07,032
Actually, saying goodbye
over the phone isn't so bad.

407
00:39:08,784 --> 00:39:10,035
Thank you,

408
00:39:11,787 --> 00:39:12,955
Seong-chan.

409
00:39:13,038 --> 00:39:14,290
Thank you too.

410
00:39:15,458 --> 00:39:16,292
Bye.

411
00:39:30,055 --> 00:39:31,223
Please come over here.

412
00:39:36,145 --> 00:39:38,439
Happy New Year.

413
00:40:53,722 --> 00:40:57,393
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
NOVEMBER 9, 2024

414
00:41:27,423 --> 00:41:29,341
Is a half-open drawer

415
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:32,386
really that big a deal?

416
00:41:34,847 --> 00:41:36,140
Is this…

417
00:41:39,059 --> 00:41:41,145
Is this supposed to be…

418
00:41:42,563 --> 00:41:44,273
this painful?

419
00:41:46,859 --> 00:41:49,945
Dad can barely breathe,
as if he's running a marathon,

420
00:41:50,029 --> 00:41:51,947
and here you are complaining…

421
00:42:05,419 --> 00:42:06,503
I'm on my way.

422
00:42:06,587 --> 00:42:07,588
No, it's fine.

423
00:42:08,505 --> 00:42:09,965
Let's not meet up today.

424
00:42:28,525 --> 00:42:30,361
Owner of car 2017?

425
00:42:39,953 --> 00:42:41,288
Owner of car 2017?

426
00:42:42,498 --> 00:42:43,999
Hello? Anyone home?

427
00:42:45,793 --> 00:42:47,211
Owner of car 2017?

428
00:42:47,294 --> 00:42:48,754
A-sol?

429
00:42:50,130 --> 00:42:51,423
What's wrong?

430
00:42:52,216 --> 00:42:54,385
I need to get my car out,
but no one's answering.

431
00:43:01,558 --> 00:43:03,852
Hi, Mom. I'm busy right now,
so I'll call you back…

432
00:43:08,649 --> 00:43:09,692
Yeah.

433
00:43:10,442 --> 00:43:12,695
No, I'm not busy. I'll be right there.

434
00:43:14,363 --> 00:43:15,364
Mom, don't cry.

435
00:43:17,366 --> 00:43:18,409
Okay, bye.

436
00:43:21,829 --> 00:43:23,038
The car…

437
00:43:23,789 --> 00:43:25,207
Tell them to move it.

438
00:43:26,333 --> 00:43:29,253
I need to go to my dad right away.

439
00:43:33,841 --> 00:43:34,675
A-sol.

440
00:44:03,328 --> 00:44:05,998
He's okay for now.

441
00:44:08,333 --> 00:44:11,795
My mom said he'll have bouts like this,
and then recover again,

442
00:44:11,879 --> 00:44:13,672
so she asked me to bring some clothes.

443
00:44:14,256 --> 00:44:15,507
Is there anything I can do?

444
00:44:16,341 --> 00:44:17,968
I left it at your house.

445
00:44:19,928 --> 00:44:21,263
But I wasn't expecting this.

446
00:44:22,181 --> 00:44:23,682
You'll see when you go home.

447
00:44:24,266 --> 00:44:27,311
I took it there
so you could work on it slowly,

448
00:44:29,229 --> 00:44:30,856
but I think you'll have to hurry.

449
00:44:33,650 --> 00:44:34,568
Okay.

450
00:44:35,652 --> 00:44:36,695
I'll get going.

451
00:44:37,946 --> 00:44:39,072
Tae-seo.

452
00:44:40,491 --> 00:44:41,909
A few days ago,

453
00:44:41,992 --> 00:44:43,786
that person with the bicycle…

454
00:44:46,163 --> 00:44:47,998
She came to your house.

455
00:44:50,209 --> 00:44:52,711
All I had to do was pick up my car,

456
00:44:52,795 --> 00:44:55,047
but I went up to your house like a fool

457
00:44:56,298 --> 00:44:57,508
and entered the passcode.

458
00:44:59,384 --> 00:45:01,553
When I went back down, she wasn't there.

459
00:45:02,137 --> 00:45:03,639
I must've been out of my mind.

460
00:45:10,687 --> 00:45:11,522
I'm sorry.

461
00:45:17,444 --> 00:45:18,362
Tae-seo.

462
00:45:19,780 --> 00:45:21,573
It's my turn to hear it.

463
00:45:24,117 --> 00:45:26,036
I really need to be ready now.

464
00:45:27,204 --> 00:45:28,747
I don't have…

465
00:45:30,249 --> 00:45:32,584
I don't have much time.

466
00:45:35,587 --> 00:45:38,632
Tell me what you want to thank me for

467
00:45:39,841 --> 00:45:41,093
right now.

468
00:45:42,010 --> 00:45:43,387
I want to hear it now.

469
00:45:53,772 --> 00:45:56,567
Do you want to take a walk?

470
00:46:15,377 --> 00:46:16,378
The reason

471
00:46:17,879 --> 00:46:19,131
why I'm grateful to you is,

472
00:46:23,051 --> 00:46:24,303
thanks to you,

473
00:46:26,888 --> 00:46:29,016
I can now hope for a warm goodbye.

474
00:46:33,270 --> 00:46:34,396
As you know…

475
00:47:18,190 --> 00:47:22,027
If the three moments of waiting
that are needed to make a frame

476
00:47:22,110 --> 00:47:23,987
can all be done in a day…

477
00:47:25,572 --> 00:47:28,492
-That thing I mentioned before…
-You mean my name tag?

478
00:47:28,575 --> 00:47:30,827
JULY 2014

479
00:47:30,911 --> 00:47:31,745
Thanks.

480
00:47:31,828 --> 00:47:34,331
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

481
00:47:37,709 --> 00:47:38,669
…I'll believe

482
00:47:40,170 --> 00:47:42,923
that the sincere and heartfelt support
I gave you back then

483
00:47:43,006 --> 00:47:47,636
went around and found its way back to me.

484
00:47:56,186 --> 00:47:58,563
Please use hanji for the mat

485
00:47:58,647 --> 00:48:00,482
and oak for the frame.

486
00:48:01,858 --> 00:48:05,821
I want it to feel like my dad's face
is being warmly embraced.

487
00:48:09,491 --> 00:48:10,534
I'm counting on you.

488
00:48:44,192 --> 00:48:46,194
The snow has let up.

489
00:48:51,324 --> 00:48:55,328
It seems it was snowing earlier
for your grandma.

490
00:49:00,333 --> 00:49:03,253
Hui-seo's grandma's memory
keeps coming and going?

491
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:06,089
They said her brain is still recovering.

492
00:49:06,173 --> 00:49:09,176
For now, her memory will be mixed up,
but it'll come back again.

493
00:49:12,679 --> 00:49:16,099
When you get old,
ten years ago feels like yesterday,

494
00:49:16,183 --> 00:49:18,727
and yesterday feels distant.

495
00:49:20,520 --> 00:49:21,897
Your mind is all over the place.

496
00:49:25,817 --> 00:49:27,194
They're coming.

497
00:49:51,760 --> 00:49:52,969
Where is she?

498
00:49:53,053 --> 00:49:55,096
I'm right here.

499
00:49:56,348 --> 00:49:57,474
Welcome back.

500
00:49:59,559 --> 00:50:00,393
Where's Eun-a?

501
00:50:02,729 --> 00:50:04,815
Eun-a is from ten years ago.

502
00:50:06,024 --> 00:50:07,567
Hwa-sun.

503
00:50:07,651 --> 00:50:08,902
What do you want with Eun-a?

504
00:50:13,949 --> 00:50:15,450
Eun-a.

505
00:50:18,119 --> 00:50:19,996
Eun-a!

506
00:50:26,169 --> 00:50:27,254
Eun-a.

507
00:50:28,839 --> 00:50:30,298
Give me your hands.

508
00:50:30,382 --> 00:50:32,968
Gosh, you were clearing the snow.

509
00:50:33,051 --> 00:50:34,678
Are you all right?

510
00:50:37,514 --> 00:50:41,226
To her, today's the day
you cleared the snow.

511
00:50:43,103 --> 00:50:44,938
You think Tae-seo made it there, okay?

512
00:50:45,021 --> 00:50:47,232
Gosh, I don't know. I'm worried.

513
00:50:55,198 --> 00:50:58,618
You cleared all the snow from our truck.

514
00:50:59,327 --> 00:51:01,705
We had to send Tae-seo off
to the military all on his own.

515
00:51:02,581 --> 00:51:05,250
There was nothing we could do.

516
00:51:08,086 --> 00:51:09,838
Did it hurt?

517
00:51:12,007 --> 00:51:15,594
It hurt really badly,
but I'm all better now.

518
00:51:16,386 --> 00:51:17,929
That's good.

519
00:51:18,013 --> 00:51:19,848
Well done.

520
00:51:19,931 --> 00:51:21,433
I heard you're going to Hawaii.

521
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:25,103
Have a safe trip.

522
00:51:25,186 --> 00:51:30,150
We'll check in on your dad often
so he doesn't feel too lonely.

523
00:51:31,568 --> 00:51:35,155
I meant to tell you this.
It's been weighing on my heart.

524
00:51:38,575 --> 00:51:40,577
Thank you.

525
00:52:16,905 --> 00:52:18,073
Grandma?

526
00:52:19,157 --> 00:52:20,450
It's me, Tae-seo.

527
00:52:21,284 --> 00:52:22,494
You remember me, right?

528
00:52:23,244 --> 00:52:24,788
Why wouldn't I remember you?

529
00:52:25,705 --> 00:52:27,290
I'm back home safe and sound.

530
00:52:32,212 --> 00:52:33,421
Eun-a!

531
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:39,177
My grandma's back.

532
00:52:39,260 --> 00:52:41,471
-Not from ten years ago. From right now.
-What?

533
00:52:42,681 --> 00:52:43,765
Get on.

534
00:52:43,848 --> 00:52:45,892
It's right now. The present!

535
00:52:45,976 --> 00:52:47,894
Yeah, I understand.

536
00:52:52,399 --> 00:52:55,402
The Hangang River
has a lot of bridges, doesn't it?

537
00:52:55,485 --> 00:52:56,736
It's so long.

538
00:52:57,737 --> 00:52:58,780
You run there every day?

539
00:52:59,823 --> 00:53:02,534
I'm usually sitting down
when I'm operating trains,

540
00:53:03,827 --> 00:53:06,121
so it's a way for me to exercise.

541
00:53:07,247 --> 00:53:08,248
Right. Good idea.

542
00:53:08,331 --> 00:53:11,126
You need to look after your health
while you work.

543
00:53:12,252 --> 00:53:13,545
Goodness, Eun-a!

544
00:53:14,212 --> 00:53:15,630
How are you?

545
00:53:17,882 --> 00:53:20,301
Eun-a. Gosh, Eun-a.

546
00:53:20,385 --> 00:53:21,678
Welcome back.

547
00:53:22,846 --> 00:53:25,015
You haven't changed one bit.

548
00:53:26,016 --> 00:53:27,892
You're the same as well.

549
00:53:29,185 --> 00:53:31,479
I'll redo your scarf for you.

550
00:53:33,106 --> 00:53:37,235
Wrap it round and around, and then tie it.

551
00:53:37,902 --> 00:53:39,237
There. Nice and warm.

552
00:53:41,698 --> 00:53:45,785
Everyone here worried about you so much.

553
00:53:45,869 --> 00:53:48,538
It's so good that you came back.

554
00:53:48,621 --> 00:53:49,831
Well done.

555
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:16,608
I'll see you off tomorrow.

556
00:54:17,525 --> 00:54:18,735
Let's say goodbye in person.

557
00:54:31,081 --> 00:54:32,373
-Granny.
-Yeah?

558
00:54:32,457 --> 00:54:34,125
You have to live well even without me.

559
00:54:34,793 --> 00:54:36,419
It'll feel empty when I'm suddenly gone.

560
00:54:36,920 --> 00:54:37,754
You're right.

561
00:54:37,837 --> 00:54:40,006
It's been like a picnic lately,

562
00:54:40,090 --> 00:54:42,092
eating and sleeping together every day.

563
00:54:42,717 --> 00:54:44,803
But after a picnic,
you need to go live your life.

564
00:54:45,428 --> 00:54:47,889
You can't keep pining for it forever.

565
00:54:48,473 --> 00:54:49,724
You're right.

566
00:54:55,563 --> 00:54:56,981
Thanks, Granny.

567
00:55:03,196 --> 00:55:04,114
Let's take a photo.

568
00:55:04,197 --> 00:55:05,990
-A photo?
-Yeah.

569
00:55:06,074 --> 00:55:07,659
Photos look nicer with plants.

570
00:55:11,079 --> 00:55:13,540
-I'm going to look at this every day.
-Okay.

571
00:55:14,374 --> 00:55:16,209
Smile and say "Eun-a."

572
00:55:16,793 --> 00:55:19,921
Mo Eun-a.

573
00:55:24,217 --> 00:55:27,262
So beautiful.
I'm going to look at this photo every day.

574
00:55:52,662 --> 00:55:55,665
I'll come to Dongjak Station.

575
00:56:00,712 --> 00:56:03,214
Dongjak Station to Incheon is too short.

576
00:57:30,510 --> 00:57:31,553
YEON NAMSAN

577
00:57:36,391 --> 00:57:38,685
These are the views
from my everyday routine.

578
00:57:41,396 --> 00:57:42,730
You wanted to see them too.

579
00:57:59,247 --> 00:58:00,081
I'm…

580
00:58:01,624 --> 00:58:04,669
going to do what we talked about together.

581
00:58:06,921 --> 00:58:09,007
You're the reason I could make up my mind,

582
00:58:09,591 --> 00:58:11,301
so I'll wait for you there.

583
00:58:12,135 --> 00:58:17,223
You should go there,
be loved and appreciated,

584
00:58:17,307 --> 00:58:18,891
and live a great life.

585
00:58:19,726 --> 00:58:21,144
And when you ever feel like

586
00:58:21,811 --> 00:58:24,147
thinking about a future that includes me,

587
00:58:25,690 --> 00:58:26,941
let me know.

588
00:58:53,468 --> 00:58:55,178
Let's say goodbye here.

589
00:59:05,313 --> 00:59:06,814
Thank you for seeing me off.

590
00:59:08,775 --> 00:59:09,609
This is…

591
00:59:11,402 --> 00:59:13,738
the first time
we're saying goodbye in person.

592
00:59:18,868 --> 00:59:20,411
Goodbye then.

593
00:59:31,839 --> 00:59:32,799
Goodbye.

594
01:00:00,326 --> 01:00:01,619
I love you,

595
01:00:05,039 --> 01:00:05,998
Mo Eun-a.

596
01:00:39,031 --> 01:00:42,410
Ladies and gentlemen, the next station is…

597
01:00:55,339 --> 01:00:57,800
Please take a moment
to look out the window.

598
01:01:14,859 --> 01:01:16,944
An ordinary view from our lives

599
01:01:18,946 --> 01:01:20,865
may become an unforgettable brilliance

600
01:01:22,575 --> 01:01:23,785
that could lead you somewhere,

601
01:01:26,162 --> 01:01:27,371
somehow,

602
01:01:28,581 --> 01:01:30,249
and to someone.

603
01:01:34,796 --> 01:01:36,172
I hope that today

604
01:01:36,255 --> 01:01:38,341
was another meaningful day

605
01:01:39,592 --> 01:01:41,511
where you followed
the shining light within you.

606
01:01:43,763 --> 01:01:44,806
You did a wonderful job

607
01:01:46,474 --> 01:01:48,059
getting through the day.

608
01:01:53,773 --> 01:01:55,525
The next station is…

609
01:02:05,576 --> 01:02:10,373
1 YEAR LATER

610
01:02:36,774 --> 01:02:40,111
CHEONGGYEONG STATION

611
01:03:49,263 --> 01:03:56,228
MO EUN-A

612
01:04:37,228 --> 01:04:38,562
Where we'll be…

613
01:04:38,646 --> 01:04:40,022
Where we'll be…

614
01:04:41,649 --> 01:04:44,360
-What we'll be doing…
-What we'll be doing…

615
01:04:48,155 --> 01:04:50,533
-And with who.
-And with who.

616
01:04:50,616 --> 01:04:54,870
STILL SHINING

617
01:04:55,454 --> 01:04:58,874
STILL SHINING

618
01:06:03,481 --> 01:06:05,483
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
